w.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aConstitutional historyzUnited States. 0aEqual rights amendmentszUnited States. 0aWomenxLegal status, laws, etczUnited StatesxHistory. 0aWomen's rightszUnited States. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh1 aAiyetoro, Adjoa A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlbertson Fineman, Martha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBasch, Norma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerkin, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoris, Eileen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper Davis, Peggy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox Piven, Frances, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGould, Carol C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarrison, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewis, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMansbridge, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNussbaum, Martha C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeach, Lucinda Joy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aResnik, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichards, David A. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneider, Elizabeth M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwarzenbach, Sibyl A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwarzenbach, Sibyl, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSmith, Patricia, 